  <source>Hellenic Oncology Research Group</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This trial will determine the feasibility and toxicity of dose intense (every 2 weeks) of
      paclitaxel+carboplatin combination following cytoreductive surgery in patients with stage
      Ic-IV ovarian cancer.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Dose dense chemotherapy has been proven beneficial in various oncological settings. It is
      proposed that this concept be tested in ovarian cancer, with the support of growth factors.
      It is hypothesized that, if feasible, dose-dense chemotherapy may be more effective.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
